  "updateinfo_id": "ALSA-2025:4048",
  "description": "XML-RPC is a remote procedure call (RPC) protocol that uses XML to encode its calls and HTTP as a transport mechanism. The xmlrpc-c packages provide a network protocol to allow a client program to make a simple RPC (remote procedure call) over the Internet. It converts an RPC into an XML document, sends it to a remote server using HTTP, and gets back the response in XML.  \n\nSecurity Fix(es):  \n\n  * libexpat: expat: Improper Restriction of XML Entity Expansion Depth in libexpat (CVE-2024-8176)\n\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n",
  "fromstr": "packager@almalinux.org",
